<span id="freeTextContainer16556420822590027903">This was not a bad book, but I did not find the story as enthralling as the first three books in the Pendragon series. The first three seem to tell a tight, cohesive story that was completely fascinating. Unfortunately, this book felt like an afterthought. It may have been since it was published more than five years after Arthur (Book 3).<br/><br/>While I don&apos;t think it is wasted time to read Pendragon, you may be disappointed if you really like the first three. I am now debating about whether I should re</span>
  <span id="freeText16556420822590027903" style="display:none">This was not a bad book, but I did not find the story as enthralling as the first three books in the Pendragon series. The first three seem to tell a tight, cohesive story that was completely fascinating. Unfortunately, this book felt like an afterthought. It may have been since it was published more than five years after Arthur (Book 3).<br /><br />While I don't think it is wasted time to read Pendragon, you may be disappointed if you really like the first three. I am now debating about whether I should read the fifth book in the series: Grail. I will wait a few weeks before making that decision.</span>
