<div id="review_1176635517" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1176635517" />
    <a title="Michael Davies" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/20163136-michael-davies"><img alt="Michael Davies" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1458300498p2/20163136.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1176635517?book_show_action=true">Jan 22, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Michael Davies" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Michael Davies" href="/user/show/20163136-michael-davies">Michael Davies</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1176635517" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer451330172403724883">I love this series. It draws upon a rich backdrop of Arthurian and Atlantean mythology. This is placed in a well researched historical and cultural context that adds depth to the world which you are reading. Add to this well thought out characters and you have the recipe for success.<br/><br/>The fourth book in the series focusses more on Arthur as King, but it&apos;s not just a repeat of past tales. It is something unique and thoroughly enjoyable. I&apos;ve re read the entire cycle many times and will do so again </span>
  <span id="freeText451330172403724883" style="display:none">I love this series. It draws upon a rich backdrop of Arthurian and Atlantean mythology. This is placed in a well researched historical and cultural context that adds depth to the world which you are reading. Add to this well thought out characters and you have the recipe for success.<br /><br />The fourth book in the series focusses more on Arthur as King, but it's not just a repeat of past tales. It is something unique and thoroughly enjoyable. I've re read the entire cycle many times and will do so again in the future. </span>
  <a data-text-id="451330172403724883" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
