        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1405121757" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15272977745979733934">This book is a bit like an appendix to the third book of this series, Arthur. It is made up of two stories: a short tale of Arthur&apos;s boyhood and the main story of Arthur dealing with a Vandal invasion. The main story about the Vandals was unified and cohesive, although one of the &quot;surprise&quot; plot developments was so obvious. You have to wonder how the great King Arthur and his wise counselor Merlin didn&apos;t foresee something so blindingly obvious. Overall though, I thought this was a bit better the</span>
  <span id="freeText15272977745979733934" style="display:none">This book is a bit like an appendix to the third book of this series, Arthur. It is made up of two stories: a short tale of Arthur's boyhood and the main story of Arthur dealing with a Vandal invasion. The main story about the Vandals was unified and cohesive, although one of the "surprise" plot developments was so obvious. You have to wonder how the great King Arthur and his wise counselor Merlin didn't foresee something so blindingly obvious. Overall though, I thought this was a bit better then the third book, Arthur.</span>
