<div id="review_47116619" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/47116619" />
    <a title="Jeannie Glanville " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2052379-jeannie-glanville"><img alt="Jeannie Glanville " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1619761629p2/2052379.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/47116619?book_show_action=true">Feb 21, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jeannie Glanville " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jeannie Glanville " href="/user/show/2052379-jeannie-glanville">Jeannie Glanville </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2052379-jeannie-glanville?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2052379-jeannie-glanville?shelf=arthur">arthur</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer47116619" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6238812980115081125">Pendragon brings into the story our Queen, Gwenhyver. Sooooooo different! But I love it! Arthur needed a Queen who was as strong as he was, as fearless a leader. I adore her in this version of the story. I think the best part is the wedding, as she and her warriors march into the wedding in full battle dress according to the tribe she belonged to. I loved it! So different from the weeping, melting, fickle blonde soft woman described by so many other authors. Hail to the White Spirit!</span>

          </span>
        </div>


